The paper deals with the complexity of propositional logics and their deductive systems, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the complexity of deductive systems for propositional logics. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper mentions the common-knowledge epistemic logic, which is a popular logic used in AI. 

cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper discusses the PSPACE-completeness of certain logics. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper uses proof-theory and the sub-formula principle to analyze the complexity of propositional logics. 

cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a possible category as the paper deals with the complexity of deductive systems for propositional logics, which can be relevant to programming language semantics.
